OL,3,CFrost found on volcanoes near Mars'
OL,4,Cequator for first time
OL,6,FMorning frost has been spotted on
OL,7,Fvolcanoes near Mars' equator for the
OL,8,Ffirst time, a part of the planet where
OL,9,Fit was thought impossible for water
OL,10,Ffrost to exist.
OL,12,FThe "astonishing" discovery confirms
OL,13,Fthat ice is not only confined to the
OL,14,Fred planet's poles, but suggests there
OL,15,Fis more water ice across the planet
OL,16,Fthan previously thought.
OL,18,FThe frost sits on top of the Tharsis `
OL,19,Fthe tallest volcanoes in the Solar
OL,20,FSystem.
